And then last, as we just got through discussing the new standard, at least in the United States

00:01:49.140 --> 00:01:55.560
and elsewhere, Nivo AVD. But of course, there are still contexts where BV can and should be

00:01:55.560 --> 00:02:02.780
considered, as was also alluded to. So the first scenario is an early stage unfavorable Hodgkin

00:02:02.780 --> 00:02:09.060
lymphoma population for which combined modality therapy has shown a consistent but modest benefit

00:02:09.060 --> 00:02:16.620
over chemotherapy alone. And two important trials to note are first the breach trial, where BV AVD

00:02:16.620 --> 00:02:25.300
was given for four cycles, followed by 30 gray of involved node radiotherapy versus ABVD plus

00:02:25.460 --> 00:02:33.800
radiation. And the primary outcome of this trial being interim pet CR rate was increased. However,

00:02:33.800 --> 00:02:41.840
the overall survival outcomes like progression free survival were very similar. A separate US

00:02:41.840 --> 00:02:48.920
phase two study attempted to address the role of radiation specifically in the with BV AVD

00:02:48.920 --> 00:02:55.360
treatment, where individuals were all treated with BV AVD for four cycles, and then randomized to

00:02:55.360 --> 00:03:03.600
one of three different radiation strategies, and a fourth strategy of observation without radiation

00:03:04.180 --> 00:03:09.760
without radiation at all. So interestingly, two year progression free survival was similar,

00:03:10.040 --> 00:03:16.780
irrespective of the radiation strategy. Multiple other non randomized studies have suggested that BV

00:03:16.780 --> 00:03:23.360
